article.headline: Wright St. 53, Wis.-Milwaukee 51
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio (AP) -- Vaughn Duggins scored with 0.4 seconds left to give Wright State a 53-51 win over Wisconsin-Milwaukee Saturday night. Wright State (14-6, 7-4 Horizon League) used a 17-3 run early in the second half to go ahead by seven with 11:48 to play. But Wisconsin-Milwaukee (12-10, 7-5) tied it at 51 with eight seconds remaining on a Marcus Skinner tip-in. The Raiders pushed back down the floor, with Duggins driving inside and scoring on a bank shot just before the buzzer. Duggins finished with 17 points and Scottie Wilson added 12 for Wright State. Skinner had 16 points and eight rebounds while Paige Paulsen, Ricky Franklin and Allan Hanson each had eight points for the Panthers.
